HEADWORD: Disexercise
<hw>Dis*ex"er*cise</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To deprive
of exercise; to leave untrained.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>By <qex>disexercising</qex> and blunting our abilities.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Disfame</ent>⟦br⟧
